verses.text: He that is wounded in the stones , or hath his privy member cut off , shall not enter into the congregation of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

A bastard shall not enter into the congregation of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; even to his tenth generation shall he not enter into the congregation of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.

An Ammonite or Moabite shall not enter into the congregation of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*; even to their tenth generation shall they not enter into the congregation of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* for ever :
Because they met you not with bread and with water in the way , when ye came forth out of Egypt ; and because they hired against thee Balaam the son of Beor of Pethor of Mesopotamia , to curse thee.

Nevertheless the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God would not hearken unto Balaam ; but the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God turned the curse into a blessing unto thee, because the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God loved thee.
Thou shalt not seek their peace nor their prosperity all thy days for ever.\f + \fr 23.6 \ft prosperity: Heb. good\f* \p
¶ Thou shalt not abhor an Edomite ; for he \add is\add* thy brother : thou shalt not abhor an Egyptian ; because thou wast a stranger in his land.
The children that are begotten of them shall enter into the congregation of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in their third generation. \p
¶ When the host goeth forth against thine enemies , then keep thee from every wicked thing. \p
¶ If there be among you any man , that is not clean by reason of uncleanness that chanceth him by night , then shall he go abroad out of the camp , he shall not come within the camp :

But it shall be, when evening cometh on , he shall wash \add himself\add* with water : and when the sun is down , he shall come into the camp \add again\add*.\f + \fr 23.11 \ft cometh…: Heb. turneth toward\f* \p
¶ Thou shalt have a place also without the camp , whither thou shalt go forth abroad :

And thou shalt have a paddle upon thy weapon ; and it shall be, when thou wilt ease thyself abroad , thou shalt dig therewith, and shalt turn back and cover that which cometh from thee:\f + \fr 23.13 \ft wilt…: Heb. sittest down\f*

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God walketh in the midst of thy camp , to deliver thee, and to give up thine enemies before thee; therefore shall thy camp be holy : that he see no unclean thing in thee, and turn away from thee.\f + \fr 23.14 \ft unclean…: Heb. nakedness of any thing\f* \p
¶ Thou shalt not deliver unto his master the servant which is escaped from his master unto thee:

He shall dwell with thee, \add even\add* among you, in that place which he shall choose in one of thy gates , where it liketh him best : thou shalt not oppress him.\f + \fr 23.16 \ft liketh…: Heb. is good for him\f* \p
¶ There shall be no whore of the daughters of Israel , nor a sodomite of the sons of Israel.\f + \fr 23.17 \ft whore: or, sodomitess\f*

Thou shalt not bring the hire of a whore , or the price of a dog , into the house of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God for any vow : for even both these \add are\add* abomination unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God. \p
¶ Thou shalt not lend upon usury to thy brother ; usury of money , usury of victuals , usury of any thing that is lent upon usury :

Unto a stranger thou mayest lend upon usury ; but unto thy brother thou shalt not lend upon usury : that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God may bless thee in all that thou settest thine hand to in the land whither thou goest to possess it. \p

¶ When thou shalt vow a vow unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , thou shalt not slack to pay it: for the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God will surely require it of thee; and it would be sin in thee.
But if thou shalt forbear to vow , it shall be no sin in thee.

That which is gone out of thy lips thou shalt keep and perform ; \add even\add* a freewill offering , according as thou hast vowed unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , which thou hast promised with thy mouth. \p
¶ When thou comest into thy neighbour’s vineyard , then thou mayest eat grapes thy fill at thine own pleasure ; but thou shalt not put \add any\add* in thy vessel.
When thou comest into the standing corn of thy neighbour , then thou mayest pluck the ears with thine hand ; but thou shalt not move a sickle unto thy neighbour’s standing corn.
